  <original-body>Pre-2.3.2 ActionController::Base.expires_in example:

  expires_in 10.minutes, :private =&gt; false

Rails 2.3.2 version:

  expires_in 10.minutes, :public =&gt; true

&quot;:private&quot; option is ignored. This breaks cache headers for upgraded apps. There is no deprecation warning either.

You can read all about my outrage over here: http://geekblog.vodpod.com/?p=224</original-body>
